# Sentinella — Cursor project rules

Sentinella is a mobile-first travel safety and security app for a specific group of
travelers in Italy. It is a Next.js 14 (App Router) PWA deployed on Railway with a
Railway PostgreSQL database. Access to personal features is gated by invite-code
registration; safety-critical content (emergency numbers, guide) is public and works
offline by design.

## Stack
- Next.js 14 App Router + TypeScript (strict), directory: src/
- Tailwind CSS with a custom token system (see tailwind.config.ts)
- Drizzle ORM + node-postgres (pg); schema in src/db/schema.ts; migrations in drizzle/
- Auth: signed JWT (jose, HS256) in an httpOnly cookie; bcryptjs password hashing;
  gate lives in src/middleware.ts
- PWA: public/manifest.json + hand-written public/sw.js (no workbox)

## Commands
- npm run dev            — local dev server
- npm run build          — production build
- npm run typecheck      — tsc --noEmit
- npm run db:generate    — generate SQL migrations from schema changes
- npm run db:migrate     — apply migrations (needs DATABASE_URL)
- npm run db:push        — dev-only schema sync
- npm run db:seed        — seed sample alerts

## Environment
DATABASE_URL, AUTH_SECRET, INVITE_CODES (comma-separated), ADMIN_EMAILS
(comma-separated). Never hardcode or commit these. .env is gitignored.

## Non-negotiable conventions
1. Signal red (`signal` token) is reserved for emergency actions only — if it's red,
   tapping it summons help. Never use it decoratively. Green (`verde`) is the working
   color; `ambra` marks caution.
2. Emergency and guide content lives in src/data/*.ts as typed static data so it is
   bundled and available offline. Do not move it into the database.
3. Never put safety-critical screens (/emergency, /guide) behind auth.
4. Touch targets are at least 44–48px (min-h-[2.75rem] or larger); keep visible
   focus states; respect prefers-reduced-motion.
5. All API input is validated with zod; auth is re-checked inside handlers even when
   middleware already gates the route.
6. When changing src/db/schema.ts, run npm run db:generate and commit the new files
   in drizzle/ — Railway applies them on deploy via npm run start:railway.
7. Any hardcoded phone numbers (embassies, poison control) must keep their
   "verify against official sources" caveat in the UI.
8. UI copy: plain verbs, sentence case, specific instructions. Errors say what
   happened and what to do next.

## Layout language
Signage plates (.plate + CallPlate component) are the signature element — emergency
numbers rendered like Italian road signs with large monospace numerals. Keep new
surfaces consistent with this system rather than introducing new card styles.
